
*Movie Search Web App
This web application allows users to search for movies and view their details, including the movie poster, title, overview, and watch trailers. Users can also add comments to the movies.


*Usage
Search for Movies:

Enter a movie title in the search bar.
-Click the search icon to retrieve a list of matching movies.
View Movie Details:

-Click on a movie from the search results to view details.
The details include the movie title, overview, and options to watch the trailer and add to the comments. Scroll down to view all the details.

Watch Trailer:
-Click the "Watch Trailer" button to view the movie trailer (if available).
A YouTube embedded player will be displayed with the trailer.

Add to the comment-section:
-Click the "Add Comment" button to add your comment on a particular movie

*Structure
index.html: The main HTML file containing the structure of the web page.

style.css: The CSS file for styling the web page.

script.js: The JavaScript file containing the logic for fetching movie data, displaying search results, and managing movie details.

*Dependencies
This web app relies on the The Movie Database (TMDb) API to fetch movie data.

*Credits
This project uses data from The Movie Database (TMDb).
